<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,437,823]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
The nominal genus 
<taxonomicName box="[382,561,437,462]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Porphyrochroa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[382,561,437,462]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Porphyrochroa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has generally been overlooked since it was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Melander" box="[1231,1432,437,463]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" refString="Melander, A. L. (1928) Diptera, Fam. Empididae. Genera Insectorum, 185 [1927], 1 - 434." type="journal article" year="1928">
Melander (
<number box="[1359,1423,437,463]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1928.0">1928</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith" box="[151,311,477,503]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" refString="Smith, K. G. V. (1967) Family Empididae (Empidae, Hybotidae). In: A Catalogue of the Diptera of the Americas south of the United States. Sao Paulo, Departamento de Zoologia, 67 pp." type="book" year="1967">
Smith (
<number box="[241,302,477,503]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1967.0">1967</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
considered it a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[751,909,477,502]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[751,909,477,502]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Macrostomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[929,1108,477,502]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Porphyrochroa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[929,1108,477,502]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Porphyrochroa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was finally revalidated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rafael" box="[151,316,517,543]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" refString="Rafael, J. A. (2001) Redescricao de duas especies neotropicais de Empididae (Diptera) descritas por Curran e revalidacao do genero Prophyrochroa. Iheringia, Serie Zoologia, 90, 127 - 132." type="journal article" year="2001">
Rafael (
<number box="[243,307,517,543]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2001.0">2001</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. In this paper, Rafael also transferred 
<taxonomicName authority="Curran" authorityName="Curran" box="[760,1111,517,543]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Axelempis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciventris">
<emphasis box="[760,1022,517,542]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Axelempis fasciventris</emphasis>
Curran
</taxonomicName>
to the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,437,823]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,358,557,583]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Recognition:</emphasis>
The monophyly of 
<taxonomicName box="[589,768,557,582]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Porphyrochroa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[589,768,557,582]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Porphyrochroa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on the following hypothesized synapomorphies: 
<number box="[151,164,597,623]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1.0">1</number>
) male tergite 
<number box="[331,346,597,623]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="8.0">8</number>
with only a few setae confined posterolaterally; 
<number box="[925,941,597,623]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2.0">2</number>
) male tergite 
<number box="[1105,1119,597,623]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="7.0">7</number>
with posteroventral protuberances; 
<number box="[269,284,637,663]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="3.0">3</number>
) abdomen metallic blue or blue-green in colour.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,437,823]" box="[198,956,677,703]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,353,677,703]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Description:</emphasis>
See 
<bibRefCitation author="Rafael" box="[410,746,677,703]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" refString="Rafael, J. A. &amp; Cumming, J. M. (2004) The Neotropical genera Macrostomus Wiedemann and Porphyrochroa Melander (Diptera, Empididae, Empidinae). Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 21 (3), 439 - 448." type="journal article" year="2004">
Rafael and Cumming (
<number box="[676,738,677,703]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2004.0">2004</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
for redescription.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,437,823]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,322,717,743]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Remarks:</emphasis>
The precise sister-group of the 
<taxonomicName box="[704,862,717,742]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[704,862,717,742]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Macrostomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName box="[893,1070,717,742]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Porphyrochroa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[893,1070,717,742]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Porphyrochroa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lineage is not yet defined, but possibly is near species within the New World 
<taxonomicName authority="Meigen" authorityName="Meigen" box="[735,1008,757,783]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Rhamphomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[735,904,757,782]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Rhamphomyia</emphasis>
Meigen
</taxonomicName>
, a diverse polyphyletic genus with world wide distributuion.
</paragraph>
